\title{Complex sine and cosine}
\author{alex-nelson}
\import{notation}
\date{2025-12-09}
\taxon{definition}
\meta{source}{[[lankham-2016-linear]] Section 2.3.4}

\p{Let #{z=x+\I y} be a complex number with #{x,y\in\RR}. Then we define the \define{Complex Sine} function #{\sin\colon\CC\to\CC} by
##{\sin(z) = \frac{\E^{\I z}-\E^{-\I z}}{2\I}}
Similarly we define the \define{Complex Cosine} function #{\cos\colon\CC\to\CC} by
##{\cos(z) = \frac{\E^{\I z}+\E^{-\I z}}{2\I}}}